Executive Profile
Susan L. Decker  Independent Director, Vail Resorts, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships55$255,691
Background

		Ms. Susan L. Decker, also known as Sue, has been an Independent Director of Berkshire Hathaway Inc. since May 05, 2007. Ms. Decker has been an Independent Director of Vail Resorts Inc., since September 25, 2015 and Costco Wholesale Corp. since October 13, 2004. She served as an Entrepreneur-in-Residence at Harvard Business School from 2009 to 2010. Ms. Decker was involved in case development activities, works with students and helps develop and deliver portions of the ... January 2010 Silicon Valley Immersion Program for students. She served as the President of Yahoo! Inc. (Now known as Altaba Inc.) from June 2007 to April, 2009. From June 2000 to April 2009, Ms. Decker held various executive management positions at Yahoo! Inc. Ms. Decker was responsible for all of the global business operations of the firm, including sales, product marketing, product and distribution across the three major customer groups of audience, advertisers and publishers. She served as the Head of Marketing Products Division of Advertiser & Publisher Group at Yahoo! Inc. from March 22, 2007 to June 2007 and served as its Head of the Advertiser and Publisher Group from December 2006 to June 2007. She served as the Chief Financial Officer at Yahoo! Inc. from June 2000 to June 2007 and its Executive Vice President of Finance and Administration from January 2002 to December 2006. She served as a Senior Vice President of Finance and Administration at Yahoo! Inc. from June 2000 to January 2002. She was a key participant in determining Yahoo! Inc.'s business strategy and was responsible for managing and setting all aspects of its financial and administrative direction within key functional areas, including finance, human resources, legal and investor relations. Previously, she was at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette for 14 years, where she started as an Equity Research Analyst. Before Yahoo!, she served as Equity Analyst at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette Securities Corp., Research Division for 14 years. She served as a Director of Global Equity Research at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette from 1998 to 2000 and served as its Global and Domestic Head of Research from August 1986 to May 2000. Prior to 1998, she served as a Publishing & Advertising Equity Securities Analyst for 12 years, providing coverage to institutional investors on more than 30 media, publishing and advertising stocks. She served as a Trustee of Save The Children Federation, Incorporated from March 2010 to March 8 2016. She served as a Director of Intel Corporation since November 2006 and as its Lead Director since May 2012 until May 19, 2016. She served as a Director of LegalZoom.com, Inc. since October 20, 2010. Ms. Decker served as a Director of Pixar, Inc. from June 2004 to May 2006 and The Stanford Institute for Economic Policy Research from March 2005 to May 2007. She served on the Financial Accounting Standards Advisory Council for a four-year term from January 2000 to January 2004. She received recognition by Institutional Investor magazine as a top rated analyst for ten consecutive years. She holds the Chartered Financial Analyst designation since 1989. In 2010, she received the Alumni Achievement Award, HBS's highest honor. She also was listed among the top 50 Most Powerful Women in Forbes in 2005, 2007 and 2008. She holds a Bachelor of Science degree from Tufts University with Double Majors in Computer Science and Economics. She holds a Master's degree in Business Administration from Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




