Prior to joining Yahoo, she worked at the U.S. investment bank Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette for 14 years.[3] She spent 12 years as an equity research analyst, providing coverage to institutional investors on more than 30 media, publishing, and advertising stocks.[4] In this capacity, she was listed by Institutional Investor magazine as a top rated analyst for ten consecutive years.[4] She subsequently became the global director of equity research, a $300 million operation.[3]
